4. Target Planning Layer

Once the CMO exists, the system decides how to grow a new body.

It asks:
	•	what is the target representation?
	•	what target constraints exist?
	•	what must be preserved?
	•	what losses are allowed?
	•	should output be compressed, equivalent, or elaborated?

Modes
	•	equivalence mode: preserve as much as possible
	•	compression mode: minimize while preserving invariant
	•	expansion mode: elaborate sparse source into richer target
	•	translation mode: move between representations with bounded loss
	•	adaptation mode: preserve function while changing form

Output

target_plan:
  target_representation: string
  target_class: string
  mode: equivalence | compression | expansion | translation | adaptation
  preserved_invariant: string
  allowed_losses: []
  forbidden_losses: []
  render_strategy: string


