9. Representation Classes

The translator should think in classes, not extensions.

Class A — Data

JSON, YAML, XML, CSV, SQL, graph data

Class B — Documents

Markdown, HTML, PDF, docs, specs

Class C — Code / Logic

Python, TS, DSLs, DAGs, config-as-code

Class D — Visual

diagrams, flowcharts, topology maps, UI trees

Class E — Narrative

stories, explanations, case studies, doctrine prose

Class F — Operational

playbooks, checklists, SOPs, procedures

Class G — Conversational

chat logs, interviews, transcripts, brainstorming threads

Class H — Symbolic / Compressed

schemas, invariants, semantic nodes, spectral maps

This is how Pantheon escapes file fetishism.

