10. Translation Types

Not all translations are equally dangerous.

Type I — Syntax Swap

JSON ↔ YAML
Low risk.

Type II — Structural Recast

CSV ↔ SQL table
Markdown outline ↔ JSON hierarchy
Moderate risk.

Type III — Semantic Re-expression

meeting notes ↔ action plan
diagram ↔ API schema
High value, moderate/high risk.

Type IV — Generative Rehydration

invariant phrase ↔ doctrine
transcript ↔ architecture doc
Highest value, highest risk.

Type V — Cross-Substrate Adaptation

story ↔ workflow
governance principle ↔ code policy
Extremely powerful, requires strict invariant declaration.

