17. Success Criteria

The Universal Translator is working when:
	•	meaning survives beyond original format
	•	conversions are auditable
	•	output loss is declared rather than hidden
	•	conversations can become plans, schemas, or code
	•	prose can become policy
	•	diagrams can become structure
	•	knowledge no longer gets stranded in its first vessel

That last one is the real win.

