18. Repo-ready doctrine paragraph

The Pantheon Universal Translator is a representation-invariant transformation engine. Rather than converting files directly, it extracts semantic structure from a source representation, normalizes that structure into a Canonical Meaning Object, and rehydrates it into a target representation under an explicit transformation contract. Its purpose is to preserve load-bearing meaning across syntax, documents, code, diagrams, workflows, narratives, and other substrates while making losses, inferences, and validation criteria explicit.

